<html>
  <problem>
    <title> Angular Acceleration </title>

<p>A disc is spinning about an axis passing through its center perpendicular to the page. At t=0, the angular velocity of the disc is 20 rad/s and the disc is spinning counterclockwise. The disc has constant angular acceleration, and at t = 3.0 s its angular velocity is 8.0 rad/s; the disc is still spinning counterclockwise. The disc continues to slow down at the same rate until t = 12.0 s.</p>

<img width="492" alt="BK76" src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK76.png"/>
<br/>

<p>Part 1. What are the magnitude and the direction of the angular acceleration of the disc?</p>

      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="yes" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">
			<text>2 rad/s<sup>2</sup>; into the page</text>
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">
			<text>3 rad/s<sup>2</sup>; into the page</text>
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="true">
			<text>4 rad/s<sup>2</sup>; into the page</text>
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">
			<text>5 rad/s<sup>2</sup>; into the page</text>
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">
			<text>2 rad/s<sup>2</sup>; out of the page</text>
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">
			<text>3 rad/s<sup>2</sup>; out of the page</text>
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil7" correct="false">
			<text>4 rad/s<sup>2</sup>; out of the page</text>
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil8" correct="false">
			<text>5 rad/s<sup>2</sup>; out of the page</text>
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>

<p>Part 2. What are the magnitude and the direction of the angular velocity of the disc at t = 12.0 s?</p>

